1. Little West 12th Street, at and adjoining the N.E. Corner of Tenth Avenue, as seen from Gansevoort Market Stand. Also shown on the west side of Eleventh Avenue, is pier No. 54, Hudson River, at the extremity of West 13th Street. October 1, 1928 P. L. Sperr.

2. The same, at a later date. Note the West side Express Vehicular Highway on Tenth Avenue. March 16, 1933. P. L. Sperr.
